ABOUT
About Song
My path in the Society is not one lane. It is fighting, art, bardic life, service, Chinese cultural inspiration, and building spaces where other people feel welcome too.
Be the Person You Needed to See
I grew up in the SCA from about age seven until my early teens, came back at 21, left again, and returned at 29. When I came back as an adult, heavy fighting was not even the original plan. I thought I might follow the path of combat archery and feast cooking instead. Then I put on armor, and that first day changed everything.
For a while, I was told I needed to choose between art and fighting. I tried narrowing myself down. I burned out. When I came back again, I made a quieter promise to myself: I would become the person I needed to see. Someone who showed there was room for fighting, art, service, bardic joy, and curiosity in the same life.
Now my path is all of it together.
